1
00:00:04,005 --> 00:00:06,941
⟨Luna, a literature geek, and Ryoko, a full-time housewife⟩

2
00:00:07,008 --> 00:00:10,945
⟨Two people who have solved various cases with their knowledge of literature⟩

3
00:00:11,012 --> 00:00:12,947
(Luna) We are connected.

4
00:00:13,013 --> 00:00:14,949
⟨My father had a feud with Luna→

5
00:00:15,015 --> 00:00:17,952
Having a hard time finding a password for my computer ⟩

6
00:00:18,018 --> 00:00:21,956
(Misato) Even if you don't have surgery, the success rate is 20%.

7
00:00:22,023 --> 00:00:24,458
(Luna) Do you think we can meet? (Ryoko) Don't worry about it!

8
00:00:24,525 --> 00:00:28,529
⟨Finally, the final chapter is about the fate of the two people⟩

9
00:00:39,039 --> 00:00:41,976
(Ryoko) Surgery? Your father?

10
00:00:42,042 --> 00:00:45,980
(Luna) It's often said that doctors don't take good care of themselves.

11
00:00:46,046 --> 00:00:48,482
My father always said that.

12
00:00:48,549 --> 00:00:51,986
Look at people carefully and help them if they are in trouble.

13
00:00:52,052 --> 00:00:56,991
With medical and legal knowledge, most people can be saved.

14
00:00:57,057 --> 00:01:02,930
So you should aim to be either a doctor or a lawyer.

15
00:01:02,997 --> 00:01:06,434
(Ryoko) But you also like literature, right?

16
00:01:06,500 --> 00:01:10,438
(Luna) I just think it's necessary as a study to improve reading comprehension.

17
00:01:10,504 --> 00:01:14,508
I was told clearly that literature cannot save people.

18
00:01:16,010 --> 00:01:17,945
(Tamura) Want to visit me?

19
00:01:18,012 --> 00:01:20,948
(Luna) I don't know my father's true intentions.

20
00:01:21,015 --> 00:01:22,450
(Ryoko) Real intention?

21
00:01:22,516 --> 00:01:28,456
(Luna) Computer I feel like my father's true intentions are hidden in there.

22
00:01:28,522 --> 00:01:31,459
(Ryoko) If mom says so→

23
00:01:31,525 --> 00:01:34,462
I'll try to find the password no matter what.

24
00:01:34,528 --> 00:01:35,963
(Luna) Yeah.

25
00:01:36,030 --> 00:01:37,965
Actually, he's a regular at our house →

26
00:01:38,032 --> 00:01:40,468
There's a guy who owns an art gallery in Ginza.

27
00:01:40,534 --> 00:01:44,472
We used to talk about literature here almost every night.

28
00:01:44,538 --> 00:01:46,974
(Fujiko) [“The moon is beautiful, isn’t it?” →

29
00:01:47,041 --> 00:01:51,979
I don't understand why... is said to be Soseki's famous quote.]

30
00:01:52,046 --> 00:01:53,981
[Among his works→

31
00:01:54,048 --> 00:01:57,985
There are many more wonderful expressions of love.

32
00:01:58,052 --> 00:02:00,488
(Luna) [Fujiko-san, what do you like? ]

33
00:02:00,554 --> 00:02:04,425
(2 people) [Sena's "Yume Juya"! ]

34
00:02:04,492 --> 00:02:07,428
(Luna) [Ah, together! It's the best! 〕 >> 〔Hahaha…〕

35
00:02:07,495 --> 00:02:10,931
(2 people) [“Please wait 100 years”]

36
00:02:10,998 --> 00:02:13,934
(Luna) [Ah~ That's it~! 〕 >> 〔Hahaha…〕

37
00:02:14,001 --> 00:02:16,937
(Luna's voice) Fujiko-san also loves Natsume Soseki →

38
00:02:17,004 --> 00:02:20,441
I love the town where Natsume Sensei was born →

39
00:02:20,508 --> 00:02:24,945
I even bought a house. (Ryoko) Haha... I'm a nerd that rivals my mom.

40
00:02:25,012 --> 00:02:29,450
(Luna) I've been emailing you, but I haven't received a reply.

41
00:02:29,517 --> 00:02:33,954
(Ryoko) Why don't you call her? Goodness needs to hurry.

42
00:02:34,021 --> 00:02:36,023
(Luna) That's right.

43
00:02:39,026 --> 00:02:41,962
(Ryoko) Well, it's about time for me. (Kominato) Oh, hello.

44
00:02:42,029 --> 00:02:45,966
(Tamura) Thank you for the meal too. >> Are you going back to work?

45
00:02:46,033 --> 00:02:49,970
(Tamura) I will be staying up all night writing the report.

46
00:02:50,037 --> 00:02:53,974
>> Tamura-kun, don't you think Sauchi's restaurant is a cafeteria?

47
00:02:54,041 --> 00:02:55,976
(Tamura) Huh? Hehe...

48
00:02:56,043 --> 00:02:59,046
>> No, it's not that.

49
00:03:02,550 --> 00:03:04,919
(Ryoko) What happened?

50
00:03:04,985 --> 00:03:07,421
(Luna) Fujiko-san…→

51
00:03:07,488 --> 00:03:09,924
He passed away four days ago...

52
00:03:09,990 --> 00:03:11,492
(Ryoko) What!?

53
00:03:14,995 --> 00:03:17,932
(Luna) Since suffering a cerebral infarction two years ago →

54
00:03:17,998 --> 00:03:22,436
My daughter, who lives with me, has been taking care of me for a long time.

55
00:03:22,503 --> 00:03:25,439
That alone must have been difficult →

56
00:03:25,506 --> 00:03:28,943
I was diagnosed with cancer last fall.

57
00:03:29,009 --> 00:03:30,945
(Ryoko) Who is your husband?

58
00:03:31,011 --> 00:03:33,447
(Luna) I got divorced when I was young.

59
00:03:33,514 --> 00:03:38,452
After the divorce, she raised three children by herself.

60
00:03:38,519 --> 00:03:40,955
(Ryoko) That's right...

61
00:03:41,021 --> 00:03:44,458
Ah, is this Natsumezaka?

62
00:03:44,525 --> 00:03:46,961
(Luna) According to Natsume Sensei's essay →

63
00:03:47,027 --> 00:03:50,464
It seems that your father was a landowner in this area.

64
00:03:50,531 --> 00:03:53,033
(Ryoko) Hey.

65
00:03:58,038 --> 00:04:02,476
(Ryoko) Is it a place connected to one of Japan's leading writers?

66
00:04:02,543 --> 00:04:05,913
(Luna) The most read work of yours is “Kokoro” →

67
00:04:05,980 --> 00:04:10,918
I think it can be said to be the pinnacle of Japanese novels, both in name and reality.

68
00:04:10,985 --> 00:04:14,922
A teacher I met as a university student.

69
00:04:14,989 --> 00:04:18,425
As I deepened my interaction with the teacher →

70
00:04:18,492 --> 00:04:22,930
I develop a strong interest in the life of a teacher full of mysteries.

71
00:04:22,997 --> 00:04:27,935
At the end of the Meiji era, when I returned home to take care of my father, he visited me →

72
00:04:28,002 --> 00:04:30,938
You will receive a thick letter from your teacher.

73
00:04:31,005 --> 00:04:33,941
"By the time you pick up this letter,

74
00:04:34,008 --> 00:04:36,944
I won't be in this world anymore."

75
00:04:37,011 --> 00:04:42,449
The letter that begins like this expresses the regrets and anguish that the teacher has had →

76
00:04:42,516 --> 00:04:45,519
It was written openly.

77
00:04:48,522 --> 00:04:52,960
(Luna) Betrayal, being betrayed, love and money can drive people crazy.

78
00:04:53,027 --> 00:04:56,463
Regarding human deeds depicted in literature →

79
00:04:56,530 --> 00:05:00,467
I had a good talk with Fujiko-san. (Ryoko) Wow.

80
00:05:00,534 --> 00:05:02,903
(Luna) Actually, she→

81
00:05:02,970 --> 00:05:06,907
It's like he was vaguely aware that I was a novelist.

82
00:05:06,974 --> 00:05:08,909
(Ryoko) Oh, is that so?

83
00:05:08,976 --> 00:05:12,913
(Luna) I was thinking about confessing this properly someday...

84
00:05:12,980 --> 00:05:15,983
I should have said it sooner.

85
00:05:17,985 --> 00:05:20,487
(Kikuo) Mr. Ikematsu. (Ikematsu) Ah.

86
00:05:22,489 --> 00:05:26,927
Wow~ I never thought I would be in charge of Mr. Shigehara →

87
00:05:26,994 --> 00:05:28,429
It's like a dream.

88
00:05:28,495 --> 00:05:32,433
(Kikuo) It's a lot of work for that person, but I think it's rewarding.

89
00:05:32,499 --> 00:05:37,438
What happened to the title? Ah, that's it...

90
00:05:37,504 --> 00:05:40,441
(Kikuo) Huh? Haven't you decided yet?

91
00:05:40,507 --> 00:05:45,446
There are tentative discussions about choosing the main character's name.

92
00:05:45,512 --> 00:05:48,449
Like ``Sanshiro'' or ``Anna Karenina.''

93
00:05:48,515 --> 00:05:50,517
Ah...｡

94
00:05:54,521 --> 00:05:58,959
This is my second daughter, Nanako, who has been waiting for you.

95
00:05:59,026 --> 00:06:03,397
(Luna) I'm sorry that I didn't know that you were battling an illness.

96
00:06:03,464 --> 00:06:05,399
>>No.

97
00:06:05,466 --> 00:06:06,967
please.

98
00:06:24,485 --> 00:06:26,987
(Luna) It's a beautiful garden.

99
00:06:29,490 --> 00:06:32,426
>>My mother loved this house.

100
00:06:32,493 --> 00:06:35,996
Apparently he bought it right around the time I was born.

101
00:06:38,499 --> 00:06:42,436
(Luna) She was a young and energetic person.

102
00:06:42,503 --> 00:06:45,506
(Ryoko) I wanted to meet you.

103
00:06:49,510 --> 00:06:51,445
(Luna) Who is this?

104
00:06:51,512 --> 00:06:53,447
>>This is Keisuke.

105
00:06:53,514 --> 00:06:56,450
I got remarried six months ago.

106
00:06:56,517 --> 00:06:58,452
(Luna) Remarried?

107
00:06:58,519 --> 00:07:01,455
>> We met at the hospital library→

108
00:07:01,522 --> 00:07:05,392
It seems like they hit it off after talking about Natsume Soseki.

109
00:07:05,459 --> 00:07:08,896
(Ryoko) It was a relationship that was connected through literature.

110
00:07:08,962 --> 00:07:12,900
>> At first, all my siblings were against it.

111
00:07:12,966 --> 00:07:16,403
But when I met him, he was a very nice person.

112
00:07:16,470 --> 00:07:19,406
Until my mother takes her last breath in this house →

113
00:07:19,473 --> 00:07:23,410
He stayed with me and took care of me.

114
00:07:23,477 --> 00:07:27,915
(Ryoko) So you were able to spend your last moments with the person you love.

115
00:07:27,981 --> 00:07:29,983
>> Yes.

116
00:07:33,987 --> 00:07:36,423
(Yutarou) Are you saying that all my sisters are sneaky?

117
00:07:36,490 --> 00:07:38,425
I asked my mother to buy me a house →

118
00:07:38,492 --> 00:07:40,427
Are you even paying for your child's school fees?

119
00:07:40,494 --> 00:07:42,429
(Mioko) It's okay to divide the siblings into three equal parts!

120
00:07:42,496 --> 00:07:44,431
(Mioko) Why do you think you should get more money for yourself?

121
00:07:44,498 --> 00:07:47,501
(Nanako) Stop it! The customers are coming.

122
00:07:49,002 --> 00:07:53,440
My mom's friend came to light the incense sticks.

123
00:07:53,507 --> 00:07:57,444
This is Mioko, my eldest daughter, whom my mother took care of during her life.

124
00:07:57,511 --> 00:07:59,513
This is Yutaro, my eldest son.

125
00:08:01,014 --> 00:08:04,384
I showed you something embarrassing...

126
00:08:04,451 --> 00:08:09,389
(Luna) Fujiko-san, didn't you leave a will?

127
00:08:09,456 --> 00:08:11,892
>> Found.

128
00:08:11,959 --> 00:08:15,896
I'm supposed to open it after the first seven days have passed.

129
00:08:15,963 --> 00:08:20,901
Whenever my sister and brother open their mouths, they always talk about money.

130
00:08:20,968 --> 00:08:25,405
Both of them didn't touch the nursing care and didn't even come to visit →

131
00:08:25,472 --> 00:08:31,411
I have a feeling that it's divided into three equal parts.

132
00:08:31,478 --> 00:08:34,414
(Ryoko) Is Nanako the one caring for you?

133
00:08:34,481 --> 00:08:38,418
>>That was the case until Keisuke came.

134
00:08:38,485 --> 00:08:42,923
(Ryoko) Um... what about your spouse's inheritance?

135
00:08:42,990 --> 00:08:45,926
Oh, I'm sorry for intruding.

136
00:08:45,993 --> 00:08:47,928
>>No.

137
00:08:47,995 --> 00:08:50,931
When Keisuke got married →

138
00:08:50,998 --> 00:08:54,434
He wrote me a memorandum waiving his inheritance.

139
00:08:54,501 --> 00:08:57,437
Because I don't want people to think that I'm after assets.

140
00:08:57,504 --> 00:08:59,506
(Luna) Is that so?

141
00:09:01,008 --> 00:09:02,876
Thank you for the meal.

142
00:09:02,943 --> 00:09:04,945
Sorry to bother you.

143
00:09:07,447 --> 00:09:11,885
>> Before you go home, would you mind letting me identify my mother's memento?

144
00:09:11,952 --> 00:09:14,454
I would like to share my mother's book with you.

145
00:09:21,461 --> 00:09:23,397
Keisuke-san.

146
00:09:23,463 --> 00:09:25,899
(Keisuke) Nanako-san, what about you?

147
00:09:25,966 --> 00:09:30,404
Ah, my mom's friends Luna and Ryoko.

148
00:09:30,470 --> 00:09:32,406
He came to visit me.

149
00:09:32,472 --> 00:09:34,975
My wife took care of me.

150
00:09:36,977 --> 00:09:38,912
What are you doing?

151
00:09:38,979 --> 00:09:41,415
I'm thinking of selling it soon.

152
00:09:41,481 --> 00:09:44,918
picture? What? >>It's a book.

153
00:09:44,985 --> 00:09:47,421
Well, something like this→

154
00:09:47,487 --> 00:09:50,424
I don't think it will cost you more than a penny.

155
00:09:50,490 --> 00:09:53,927
Wait, this is my mother's treasured collection.

156
00:09:53,994 --> 00:09:57,931
It is better to do the troublesome sorting of belongings quickly.

157
00:09:57,998 --> 00:10:02,436
If you are a bereaved family member, you will be emotional and will have a hard time moving forward.

158
00:10:02,502 --> 00:10:06,940
(Luna) Your husband is also a bereaved family member.

159
00:10:07,007 --> 00:10:11,445
>>Of course I'm sad too.

160
00:10:11,511 --> 00:10:15,949
But before I sell my house, I need to do some organizing.

161
00:10:16,016 --> 00:10:20,454
teeth? This house will not be sold!

162
00:10:20,520 --> 00:10:25,459
But both Mioko and Yutaro are eager to sell.

163
00:10:25,525 --> 00:10:28,962
They probably don't want to live here anymore.

164
00:10:29,029 --> 00:10:30,964
I won't let that happen.

165
00:10:31,031 --> 00:10:34,968
This is my mother's precious home.

166
00:10:35,035 --> 00:10:40,974
No, you don't have any authority in the first place.

167
00:10:41,041 --> 00:10:45,979
I will have the rights to the house and land.

168
00:10:46,046 --> 00:10:47,981
(Nanako) Yeah, but→

169
00:10:48,048 --> 00:10:51,485
Isn't this a promise to give up your inheritance?

170
00:10:51,551 --> 00:10:55,989
You wouldn't have let me marry you if I didn't say so, right?

171
00:10:56,056 --> 00:11:01,995
Legally, spouses have the right to inherit property.

172
00:11:02,062 --> 00:11:03,997
You know, right?

173
00:11:05,999 --> 00:11:07,934
(Keisuke) In the will →

174
00:11:08,001 --> 00:11:11,438
All assets including real estate and financial assets →

175
00:11:11,505 --> 00:11:13,940
It says that it will be given to me.

176
00:11:14,007 --> 00:11:16,443
I didn't ask for it.

177
00:11:16,510 --> 00:11:18,512
It's her legacy.

178
00:11:22,516 --> 00:11:26,453
(Luna) May I ask you one thing?

179
00:11:26,520 --> 00:11:28,455
>> Yes?

180
00:11:28,522 --> 00:11:32,459
(Luna) I heard that you became close friends with Natsume Soseki sensei.

181
00:11:32,526 --> 00:11:37,964
What did you and Fujiko talk about about Natsume-sensei?

182
00:11:38,031 --> 00:11:42,469
>> Even if I told you, you wouldn't understand, right?

183
00:11:42,536 --> 00:11:44,971
(Luna) Also in Natsume Sensei's works →

184
00:11:45,038 --> 00:11:48,975
There are many articles dealing with inheritance issues.

185
00:11:49,042 --> 00:11:51,978
>> Ah, that's right.

186
00:11:52,045 --> 00:11:55,982
(Luna) Which work left an impression on you?

187
00:11:56,049 --> 00:12:00,987
>> There are so many things that I can't come up with right away.

188
00:12:01,054 --> 00:12:04,424
(Luna) For example, how about "gate"?

189
00:12:04,491 --> 00:12:07,928
It looks like it's in the box as well.

190
00:12:07,994 --> 00:12:12,933
>> Ah~ “gate”! That's certainly true.

191
00:12:12,999 --> 00:12:16,436
(Luna) The same goes for ``Botchan'' and ``Kokoro.''

192
00:12:16,503 --> 00:12:20,440
>> Well, there are a lot of them.

193
00:12:20,507 --> 00:12:26,446
Keisuke-san, isn't it a lie that you like Soseki?

194
00:12:26,513 --> 00:12:28,949
It doesn't matter anymore.

195
00:12:29,015 --> 00:12:31,017
That's not a good thing!

196
00:12:33,520 --> 00:12:35,956
(Ryoko) Um... it's about time for us...

197
00:12:36,022 --> 00:12:39,960
>>He had intended to take over his house and property from the beginning.

198
00:12:40,026 --> 00:12:44,464
I was totally fooled. >> I thought it was weird.

199
00:12:44,531 --> 00:12:47,467
How dare you try to court an old lady.

200
00:12:47,534 --> 00:12:51,972
(Luna) Fujiko-san is a wonderful person.I don't think age matters.

201
00:12:52,038 --> 00:12:55,976
>>I have no intention of sharing any of my assets with you.

202
00:12:56,042 --> 00:12:57,978
I even wrote a memorandum.

203
00:12:58,044 --> 00:13:03,416
She has clearly stated in her will that she will leave all her assets to me.

204
00:13:03,483 --> 00:13:08,488
If you think it's a lie, why don't you open the will right now?

205
00:13:11,491 --> 00:13:13,493
(unlock sound)

206
00:13:15,495 --> 00:13:18,431
(Nanako) What!? >> No! The will is missing!

207
00:13:18,498 --> 00:13:20,934
Huh? (Yutaro) What?

208
00:13:21,001 --> 00:13:22,936
The safe was closed in the morning, right?

209
00:13:23,003 --> 00:13:25,438
You saw it too, right? >>Yes.

210
00:13:25,505 --> 00:13:29,943
Only you know the password.

211
00:13:30,010 --> 00:13:35,949
That means one of the three brought it up.

212
00:13:36,016 --> 00:13:38,451
Why do you bring it up?

213
00:13:38,518 --> 00:13:41,454
Look at the text that says you will entrust all your assets to me→

214
00:13:41,521 --> 00:13:44,457
I guess you hid it in a hurry. (Yutaro) Wait a minute.

215
00:13:44,524 --> 00:13:48,962
The story about letting an old man inherit all his assets is a lie!

216
00:13:49,029 --> 00:13:50,964
You brought it up!

217
00:13:51,031 --> 00:13:54,034
That's why I don't know the PIN number!

218
00:13:56,536 --> 00:13:58,972
I have no choice but to look for the will.

219
00:13:59,039 --> 00:14:02,475
If you read the contents, everything will become clear.

220
00:14:02,542 --> 00:14:07,414
(Luna) It would be better if there were no outsiders.

221
00:14:07,480 --> 00:14:09,416
(Keisuke) No, you two.

222
00:14:09,482 --> 00:14:11,918
Could you please attend the search?

223
00:14:11,985 --> 00:14:14,921
(Ryoko) What? No, we are...

224
00:14:14,988 --> 00:14:18,925
>> The person who hid the will pretended to be looking for it →

225
00:14:18,992 --> 00:14:21,928
I might dispose of it secretly.

226
00:14:21,995 --> 00:14:25,432
That's why I want you to keep an eye on me.

227
00:14:25,498 --> 00:14:27,500
(Ryoko) Watching...

228
00:14:29,502 --> 00:14:31,438
(Luna) I understand.

229
00:14:31,504 --> 00:14:35,008
Let's have a helper come here.

230
00:14:36,509 --> 00:14:39,946
(Tamura) Hello, I'm a detective. >> Hello, I'm a former detective!

231
00:14:40,013 --> 00:14:43,450
(Luna) They are good at searching houses and keeping watch.

232
00:14:43,516 --> 00:14:46,453
When I contacted them, they said they were closed, so they came.

233
00:14:46,519 --> 00:14:51,024
>>Let's get started.Let's split into two groups and search.

234
00:15:00,033 --> 00:15:02,902
(Tamura) I looked into all the places to check with the gasa container →

235
00:15:02,969 --> 00:15:05,405
I can't find it. (Ryoko) Yeah.

236
00:15:05,472 --> 00:15:10,410
>> Huh! I still had this fork.

237
00:15:10,477 --> 00:15:13,980
(Nanako) Ah, this is so nostalgic.

238
00:15:15,982 --> 00:15:20,487
There were plenty of side dishes for the whole family.

239
00:15:21,488 --> 00:15:24,924
Mom was busy with work.

240
00:15:24,991 --> 00:15:26,426
(Fujiko) [Fried egg]

241
00:15:26,493 --> 00:15:29,929
(Nanako's voice) Even so, she always made food for me.

242
00:15:29,996 --> 00:15:31,998
[Sit down and eat]

243
00:15:36,503 --> 00:15:38,438
Huh~

244
00:15:38,505 --> 00:15:42,942
What was Mom thinking in this seat?

245
00:15:43,009 --> 00:15:45,945
What should I do with food?

246
00:15:46,012 --> 00:15:48,448
That's not all, right?

247
00:15:48,515 --> 00:15:53,520
There are many things that even my family doesn't understand.

248
00:15:55,522 --> 00:15:59,459
(Tamura) Noppi's mother said that the other day.

249
00:15:59,526 --> 00:16:04,898
He said he studied a lot because he wanted to understand him.

250
00:16:04,964 --> 00:16:07,901
(Ryoko) Mom also opens the computer→

251
00:16:07,967 --> 00:16:10,904
You're trying to get to know your father.

252
00:16:10,970 --> 00:16:14,974
(Tamura) Hmm, it may have been like that at first, but...

253
00:16:16,476 --> 00:16:20,914
Right now, it looks like he's buying time and running away.

254
00:16:20,980 --> 00:16:23,917
From facing my father.

255
00:16:23,984 --> 00:16:34,928
♪～

256
00:16:34,994 --> 00:16:40,934
(Eisuke) Get rid of everything in this room.

257
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:43,937
(Misato) Huh? but….

258
00:16:44,003 --> 00:16:49,509
There's nothing better than keeping yourself light.

259
00:16:51,010 --> 00:16:56,449
The computer I was asked to dispose of the other day→

260
00:16:56,516 --> 00:16:59,953
I gave it to that kid.

261
00:17:00,019 --> 00:17:04,391
(Eisuke) Another unnecessary thing.

262
00:17:04,457 --> 00:17:06,893
Well, that's fine.

263
00:17:06,960 --> 00:17:11,398
It's password protected so I can't open it anyway.

264
00:17:11,464 --> 00:17:14,901
You might be able to solve it unexpectedly.

265
00:17:14,968 --> 00:17:18,405
Because I hate losing, just like you.

266
00:17:18,471 --> 00:17:20,473
Hmph.

267
00:17:29,983 --> 00:17:32,919
No, it's a shame that I can't put my experience to use.

268
00:17:32,986 --> 00:17:36,923
(Luna) No, I'm sorry for rushing out on your day off.

269
00:17:36,990 --> 00:17:38,425
>> Nope.

270
00:17:38,491 --> 00:17:42,929
My bar experience is quite useful, though.

271
00:17:42,996 --> 00:17:45,432
Cocktails I learned how to make with Marquee Moon →

272
00:17:45,498 --> 00:17:49,436
The other day I served it to my dad at my parents' house, and he was really happy.

273
00:17:49,502 --> 00:17:52,439
I was able to show my filial piety to my parents in an unexpected place.

274
00:17:52,505 --> 00:17:57,444
Your parents were surprised that you quit being a detective and went to work at a bar, right?

275
00:17:57,510 --> 00:18:00,447
No, surprisingly not.

276
00:18:00,513 --> 00:18:03,383
When children get older, they don't do what they want →

277
00:18:03,450 --> 00:18:05,385
I guess you'll understand.

278
00:18:05,452 --> 00:18:08,955
It's your life, so I'm telling you to do it as you like.

279
00:18:09,956 --> 00:18:12,892
(Mioko) Akko's sewing machine was still there.

280
00:18:12,959 --> 00:18:14,961
Will this work?

281
00:18:16,963 --> 00:18:20,400
My mother used to make us clothes.

282
00:18:20,467 --> 00:18:22,902
My hobby was dressmaking.

283
00:18:22,969 --> 00:18:26,406
Yes, this! nostalgic.

284
00:18:26,473 --> 00:18:28,408
(Luna) It's wonderful.

285
00:18:28,475 --> 00:18:32,412
>> But there are still a lot of things.

286
00:18:32,479 --> 00:18:34,981
I need to sort this out soon.

287
00:18:44,924 --> 00:18:49,362
Hey, this is what this room looks like right now.

288
00:18:49,429 --> 00:18:51,865
This was originally a guest room →

289
00:18:51,931 --> 00:18:55,935
I renovated it and used it as a bedroom for my mother and Keisuke.

290
00:19:03,443 --> 00:19:06,880
(Ryoko) Ah, there's a bookshelf here too.

291
00:19:06,946 --> 00:19:10,383
(Tamura) Shall we search the book room as well?

292
00:19:10,450 --> 00:19:13,887
(Ryoko) Soseki.

293
00:19:13,953 --> 00:19:18,391
``Kokoro'' ``Botchan'' ``Michigusa''.

294
00:19:18,458 --> 00:19:19,893
Well…｡

295
00:19:19,959 --> 00:19:22,395
(Tamura) Ah, it's ``Yubijinso.''

296
00:19:22,462 --> 00:19:24,397
(Ryoko) Are you tired?

297
00:19:24,464 --> 00:19:27,901
All of this was on the second floor.

298
00:19:27,967 --> 00:19:31,404
(Tamura) Two copies of the same book...

299
00:19:31,471 --> 00:19:33,406
(sound of opening curtains)

300
00:19:33,473 --> 00:19:36,843
(Yutaro) Huh? I also built a garden on this side.

301
00:19:36,910 --> 00:19:38,845
(Nanako) Ah, the backyard.

302
00:19:38,912 --> 00:19:41,848
(Ryoko) Ah, the flowers are so cute!

303
00:19:41,915 --> 00:19:43,850
It looks like your dog can play with it too.

304
00:19:43,917 --> 00:19:47,854
>> Ah, dogs aren't allowed in because there's a fence.

305
00:19:47,921 --> 00:19:50,356
(Ryoko) Ah, that's right.

306
00:19:50,423 --> 00:19:53,860
>> I left the remodeling and gardening to Keisuke →

307
00:19:53,927 --> 00:19:56,362
I don't really understand.

308
00:19:56,429 --> 00:19:59,866
Maybe he didn't like being trampled by dogs.

309
00:19:59,933 --> 00:20:03,369
Maybe he was just pretending to like dogs.

310
00:20:03,436 --> 00:20:05,438
That's definitely true.

311
00:20:07,440 --> 00:20:10,944
(Keisuke) In the end, I couldn't find it.

312
00:20:12,946 --> 00:20:14,881
I can't help it.

313
00:20:14,948 --> 00:20:19,385
I'm reluctant, but I'll settle for the legal inheritance.

314
00:20:19,452 --> 00:20:20,887
Huh?

315
00:20:20,954 --> 00:20:25,391
The spouse receives half of the amount, which is about 300 million yen.

316
00:20:25,458 --> 00:20:27,393
(whispering) 300 million.

317
00:20:27,460 --> 00:20:30,897
(Keisuke) Each of you will receive 100 million.

318
00:20:30,964 --> 00:20:32,966
It was good.

319
00:20:36,903 --> 00:20:38,838
Man, isn't that weird?

320
00:20:38,905 --> 00:20:41,341
If you can't find the will, even better, give me all your assets →

321
00:20:41,407 --> 00:20:43,343
I feel like saying that.

322
00:20:43,409 --> 00:20:48,348
(Tamura) Well, it doesn't really solve anything.

323
00:20:48,414 --> 00:20:53,353
(Luna) The will was never found, and we don't know who took it away.

324
00:20:53,419 --> 00:20:56,356
The motive too. (Dog barking)

325
00:20:56,422 --> 00:21:01,427
(Keisuke) \Hecto! Hector, what are you doing?

326
00:21:05,431 --> 00:21:08,434
I made my slippers mushy again.

327
00:21:09,936 --> 00:21:13,873
(Luna) Keisuke-san, what are you saying now?

328
00:21:13,940 --> 00:21:16,876
>> Even if you put together your slippers, they will quickly turn into a mess.

329
00:21:16,943 --> 00:21:20,380
(Luna) No, it's the dog's name.

330
00:21:20,446 --> 00:21:22,949
>> It's Hector.

331
00:21:26,953 --> 00:21:29,389
(Ryoko) Mom?

332
00:21:29,455 --> 00:21:33,459
(Luna) Maybe inside the glass door...

333
00:21:37,397 --> 00:21:39,332
(Luna) What about this room?

334
00:21:39,399 --> 00:21:42,335
(Ryoko) It was renovated as a bedroom for the couple.

335
00:21:42,402 --> 00:21:45,838
(Luna) Renovation... this might be it.

336
00:21:45,905 --> 00:21:49,342
>> Furniture with glass doors is also available on the second floor.

337
00:21:49,409 --> 00:21:51,344
(Luna) Oh, I'm sorry.

338
00:21:51,411 --> 00:21:53,346
That's not what I meant.

339
00:21:53,413 --> 00:21:57,350
Not "inside the glass door" but "inside the glass door."

340
00:21:57,417 --> 00:22:00,353
This is the title of Natsume Sensei's essay.

341
00:22:00,420 --> 00:22:23,876
♪～

342
00:22:23,943 --> 00:22:25,378
(Luna) There it was.

343
00:22:25,445 --> 00:22:27,447
>> Huh...｡ That's a lie...｡

344
00:22:38,024 --> 00:22:40,460
(Tamura) I think we're good enough.

345
00:22:40,526 --> 00:22:42,962
>>But this kid...

346
00:22:43,029 --> 00:22:44,964
Hey.

347
00:22:45,031 --> 00:22:47,467
(Luna) “Inside the glass door”→

348
00:22:47,533 --> 00:22:51,971
The story is about what happens after a thief breaks into Natsume Sensei's house.

349
00:22:52,038 --> 00:22:56,976
``Ever since that happened, I have cut the pillars in my house →

350
00:22:57,043 --> 00:23:00,980
I devised a way to hide the money I had in there."

351
00:23:01,047 --> 00:23:04,984
Fujiko, a Soseki enthusiast, is at the time of renovation →

352
00:23:05,051 --> 00:23:07,987
I thought it might have been done in the same way.

353
00:23:08,054 --> 00:23:10,923
(Tamura) What is kirigumi? >> Huh?

354
00:23:10,990 --> 00:23:13,426
The one that cuts and assembles the lumber.

355
00:23:13,493 --> 00:23:15,928
Look, it's like a sake cup. (Tamura) Ah...

356
00:23:15,995 --> 00:23:19,432
>> Why did you do that...?

357
00:23:19,499 --> 00:23:24,437
It's more like a playful desire to do the same thing as my favorite author →

358
00:23:24,504 --> 00:23:26,939
I guess it's fan psychology.

359
00:23:27,006 --> 00:23:29,942
Mom also has a fountain pen →

360
00:23:30,009 --> 00:23:33,446
I used the same one that Soseki loved.

361
00:23:33,513 --> 00:23:35,948
(Tamura) Is it like pushing?

362
00:23:36,015 --> 00:23:41,020
>> I was wondering why they put up a new decorative pillar in such a place.

363
00:23:43,523 --> 00:23:47,460
(Luna) There was probably only one person who knew about the existence of this drawer.

364
00:23:47,527 --> 00:23:49,462
After renovation →

365
00:23:49,529 --> 00:23:52,965
The person who was spending time with Fujiko in this room.

366
00:23:53,032 --> 00:23:55,968
Keisuke-san.

367
00:23:56,035 --> 00:24:00,473
(Ryoko) But he doesn't know the password for the safe.

368
00:24:00,540 --> 00:24:04,977
(Luna) Is the PIN number, for example, Fujiko's birthday?

369
00:24:05,044 --> 00:24:06,979
>> Yes, why?

370
00:24:07,046 --> 00:24:09,982
(Luna) A number that is easy for all siblings to remember.

371
00:24:10,049 --> 00:24:13,419
This is a number that is easy for Keisuke to predict.

372
00:24:13,486 --> 00:24:17,924
(Yutaro) So the old man hid the will?

373
00:24:17,990 --> 00:24:20,927
You must have thought it would be troublesome if we saw this.

374
00:24:20,993 --> 00:24:22,929
Let's open it.

375
00:24:22,995 --> 00:24:37,443
♪～

376
00:24:37,510 --> 00:24:42,448
“All of Fujiko Kosaka’s assets belong to her three children →

377
00:24:42,515 --> 00:24:47,453
My eldest daughter, Mioko, my eldest son, Yutaro, and my second daughter, Nanako →

378
00:24:47,520 --> 00:24:49,956
Inherit equally.

379
00:24:50,022 --> 00:24:56,028
The spouse, Keisuke, will not be allowed to inherit the property."

380
00:25:02,535 --> 00:25:07,473
(Ryoko) It has a handwritten date and a stamp on it.

381
00:25:07,540 --> 00:25:11,477
(Luna) It seems that there is no doubt that it is Fujiko-san's will.

382
00:25:11,544 --> 00:25:14,981
>> The old man was left out after all.

383
00:25:15,047 --> 00:25:18,484
You were trying to trick us into selling this house→

384
00:25:18,551 --> 00:25:21,487
I can't leave it there. >> Wait a moment.

385
00:25:21,554 --> 00:25:24,991
Even I can claim the remainder →

386
00:25:25,057 --> 00:25:26,993
I have the right to stay in this house.

387
00:25:27,059 --> 00:25:31,497
(Luna) Unfortunately, Keisuke-san does not have that right.

388
00:25:31,564 --> 00:25:32,999
>> Huh!?

389
00:25:33,065 --> 00:25:35,001
(Luna) Civil Code Article 891.

390
00:25:35,067 --> 00:25:40,006
Forging, altering, and destroying the decedent's will →

391
00:25:40,072 --> 00:25:44,010
Or, the person who concealed the information cannot become an heir.

392
00:25:44,076 --> 00:25:49,015
In other words, you have already lost your inheritance rights.

393
00:25:49,081 --> 00:25:52,518
>> Extra things! Because of you...

394
00:25:52,585 --> 00:25:55,521
(Luna) Keisuke was the one who gave you the hint, right?

395
00:25:55,588 --> 00:25:57,023
>> Oh?

396
00:25:57,089 --> 00:26:02,028
(Luna) With your words, I was able to discover the hidden place.

397
00:26:02,094 --> 00:26:06,532
“Hecto,” you called your dog’s name.

398
00:26:06,599 --> 00:26:09,035
>> What is that?

399
00:26:09,101 --> 00:26:12,972
(Luna) The name of the dog that Natsume-sensei loved was also ``Hecto''.

400
00:26:13,039 --> 00:26:16,976
This is also an episode that appears in ``Glass Door''.

401
00:26:17,043 --> 00:26:21,047
When I heard that name, I thought it might be a good idea.

402
00:26:23,049 --> 00:26:25,484
>> Please leave quickly!

403
00:26:25,551 --> 00:26:28,988
This is my mother's and my home.

404
00:26:29,055 --> 00:26:31,490
Why are you so particular about this house?

405
00:26:31,557 --> 00:26:36,996
The real estate agent told me that the property doesn't have much value.

406
00:26:37,063 --> 00:26:39,999
But it looks like the land can be sold at a pretty good price.

407
00:26:40,066 --> 00:26:42,501
I'll appraise it as soon as possible... No, I won't sell it!

408
00:26:42,568 --> 00:26:47,006
yeah? Yutaro and Mioko were planning to sell, right?

409
00:26:47,073 --> 00:26:48,574
I won't sell it!

410
00:26:56,082 --> 00:26:59,518
(Keisuke) I'm going to pack my things.

411
00:26:59,585 --> 00:27:02,088
all the best.

412
00:27:07,093 --> 00:27:09,528
Thanks to Mr. Nomiya and others.

413
00:27:09,595 --> 00:27:12,465
Thank you very much.

414
00:27:12,531 --> 00:27:15,034
(Mioko: Yutaro) Thank you very much.

415
00:27:20,806 --> 00:27:24,744
(Luna) Thank you for your help today, it was reassuring.

416
00:27:24,810 --> 00:27:28,247
>> No, no, okay. Then let's go have a drink.

417
00:27:28,314 --> 00:27:31,250
(Tamura) Ah, I'm going to show up at my parents' house from now on.

418
00:27:31,317 --> 00:27:33,753
Something suddenly made me want to see my parents' faces.

419
00:27:33,819 --> 00:27:36,822
(Kominato) Yeah, excuse me.

420
00:27:45,331 --> 00:27:48,768
(Ryoko) It is also said that Soseki's father is a landowner in this area →

421
00:27:48,834 --> 00:27:52,271
Maybe an episode of “Inside the Glass Door”?

422
00:27:52,338 --> 00:27:53,773
(Luna) Yes.

423
00:27:53,839 --> 00:27:57,209
(Ryoko) It's full of information on Soseki.

424
00:27:57,276 --> 00:28:02,214
There were two of those books at Fujiko-san's place, too.

425
00:28:02,281 --> 00:28:04,717
Is there such a thing as an otaku?

426
00:28:04,784 --> 00:28:08,721
(Luna) What, you mean there were two volumes of ``Inside the Glass Door''?

427
00:28:08,788 --> 00:28:11,223
(Ryoko) Yes, there were others.

428
00:28:11,290 --> 00:28:13,793
Most of them were Soseki's books.

429
00:28:16,295 --> 00:28:19,732
Ah, cute poppy.

430
00:28:19,799 --> 00:28:22,234
It was also in Fujiko's garden, right?

431
00:28:22,301 --> 00:28:25,738
(Luna) Huh? A garden like that Japanese garden?

432
00:28:25,805 --> 00:28:28,741
(Ryoko) Oh, I see. Mom isn't watching.

433
00:28:28,808 --> 00:28:33,312
There were many flowers in bloom in the backyard that I could see from my remodeled bedroom.

434
00:28:39,318 --> 00:28:42,755
(Luna) Poppy even though you have a dog?

435
00:28:42,822 --> 00:28:45,257
(Ryoko) I'm sure there is a fence →

436
00:28:45,324 --> 00:28:48,327
He said it was designed to prevent dogs from entering.

437
00:28:49,829 --> 00:28:53,766
(Luna) Do you remember the title of Natsume Sensei's two books?

438
00:28:53,833 --> 00:28:57,703
(Ryoko) Well, it's "Kokoro", right?

439
00:28:57,770 --> 00:29:01,774
``Botchan'', ``Michigusa'', and ``Yubijinso''.

440
00:29:16,288 --> 00:29:25,231
♪～

441
00:29:25,297 --> 00:29:27,233
(Luna) 《Pillar drawer...》

442
00:29:27,299 --> 00:29:31,804
(Nanako) [It's more like a playful desire to do the same thing as my favorite author...]

443
00:29:34,306 --> 00:29:36,242
(Luna) 《Poppies in the garden...》

444
00:29:36,308 --> 00:29:40,246
(Ryoko) [There is a fence so that the dog cannot enter...]

445
00:29:40,312 --> 00:29:41,747
(Luna) 《Hecto...》

446
00:29:41,814 --> 00:29:44,316
(Keisuke) [Hecto! Here Hector]

447
00:29:47,820 --> 00:29:49,755
(Luna) 《Two books...》

448
00:29:49,822 --> 00:29:53,759
>> [Keisuke-san, isn't it a lie that you like Soseki? ]

449
00:29:53,826 --> 00:30:14,213
♪～

450
00:30:14,280 --> 00:30:16,715
(Luna) We are connected.

451
00:30:16,782 --> 00:30:19,785
Ryoko, let's go back.

452
00:30:31,797 --> 00:30:34,733
>> I'll leave properly.

453
00:30:34,800 --> 00:30:37,803
I've already finished packing.

454
00:30:39,305 --> 00:30:43,309
(Luna) Could I see your backyard?

455
00:30:52,318 --> 00:30:54,320
>> Please.

456
00:30:59,325 --> 00:31:02,328
(Sound of fence closing)

457
00:31:07,833 --> 00:31:09,768
(Luna) Keisuke-san.

458
00:31:09,835 --> 00:31:12,771
Are you going to wait 100 years?

459
00:31:12,838 --> 00:31:14,773
>> Yes?

460
00:31:14,840 --> 00:31:18,777
(Luna) This is a lily, right?

461
00:31:18,844 --> 00:31:20,779
>> That's not true.

462
00:31:20,846 --> 00:31:22,781
(Luna) No, it's Yuri.

463
00:31:22,848 --> 00:31:25,284
So don't let Hector come in →

464
00:31:25,351 --> 00:31:27,286
You're putting up a fence.

465
00:31:27,353 --> 00:31:30,289
Lily is poisonous to dogs.

466
00:31:30,356 --> 00:31:32,291
Of course poppies too.

467
00:31:32,358 --> 00:31:34,793
>> I'm feeling confused again.

468
00:31:34,860 --> 00:31:36,795
(Luna) Do you want to stop now?

469
00:31:36,862 --> 00:31:40,733
Pretending not to know about Natsume-sensei.

470
00:31:40,799 --> 00:31:45,804
>> Soseki is an excuse to get closer to her.

471
00:31:47,306 --> 00:31:50,309
You were the one who peeled off my disguise, right?

472
00:31:51,810 --> 00:31:54,246
(Luna) What you peeled off was fake skin.

473
00:31:54,313 --> 00:31:57,249
I was completely fooled too.

474
00:31:57,316 --> 00:32:02,254
You are definitely a common topic of Natsume Soseki→

475
00:32:02,321 --> 00:32:05,758
Fujiko-san and I were drawn to each other.

476
00:32:05,824 --> 00:32:08,260
(Ryoko) What do you mean?

477
00:32:08,327 --> 00:32:12,331
(Luna) Another name for poppy is Yubijinso.

478
00:32:13,832 --> 00:32:17,770
There were two books each, one of which belonged to Fujiko.

479
00:32:17,836 --> 00:32:21,273
The other book was written when Keisuke moved here →

480
00:32:21,340 --> 00:32:23,776
That's what you brought, right?

481
00:32:23,842 --> 00:32:25,844
And this lily.

482
00:32:27,846 --> 00:32:32,785
``Please sit by my grave for 100 years and wait.''

483
00:32:32,851 --> 00:32:35,354
I’m sure he’ll come see you.”

484
00:32:36,855 --> 00:32:39,224
In Natsume Sensei's "Yume Juya" →

485
00:32:39,291 --> 00:32:43,228
These are the lines that a dying woman tells a man.

486
00:32:43,295 --> 00:32:49,234
100 years later, she returns as a lily.

487
00:32:49,301 --> 00:32:52,304
This is a novel that Fujiko loved.

488
00:32:54,306 --> 00:32:58,744
>> You are also quite knowledgeable.

489
00:32:58,811 --> 00:33:01,246
(Luna) Could you please tell me?

490
00:33:01,313 --> 00:33:06,318
Why did he choose to play the role of a bad guy trying to take over property?

491
00:33:12,825 --> 00:33:15,828
>>I just wanted to protect this place.

492
00:33:17,329 --> 00:33:19,264
She often →

493
00:33:19,331 --> 00:33:25,270
He told me about the memories he had with his family in this house.

494
00:33:25,337 --> 00:33:30,843
I was lonely all my life and I was jealous.

495
00:33:38,784 --> 00:33:42,721
(Keisuke) Besides, if this place disappears→

496
00:33:42,788 --> 00:33:45,724
There will be no place for Nanako to stay.

497
00:33:45,791 --> 00:33:49,728
Fujiko-san talks about Nanako-san→

498
00:33:49,795 --> 00:33:52,231
I cared about him until the end.

499
00:33:52,297 --> 00:33:54,733
It just puts effort into it →

500
00:33:54,800 --> 00:33:58,737
I'm sorry I couldn't do anything.

501
00:33:58,804 --> 00:34:03,242
Yutaro-san and Mioko-san just talked →

502
00:34:03,308 --> 00:34:06,245
He said it clearly.

503
00:34:06,311 --> 00:34:09,248
"I'm not selling my house," he said.

504
00:34:09,314 --> 00:34:11,250
I felt relieved.

505
00:34:11,316 --> 00:34:13,252
Now →

506
00:34:13,318 --> 00:34:18,257
There's no reason for me to be here anymore.

507
00:34:18,323 --> 00:34:21,260
(Luna) Keisuke-san, maybe →

508
00:34:21,326 --> 00:34:25,764
Did you call out Hector's name on purpose?

509
00:34:25,831 --> 00:34:28,267
>> Yes.

510
00:34:28,333 --> 00:34:33,772
No one found where that pillar was hidden.

511
00:34:33,839 --> 00:34:39,711
The story cannot proceed unless the will is produced.

512
00:34:39,778 --> 00:34:42,714
If you are familiar with Soseki→

513
00:34:42,781 --> 00:34:45,717
From the episode “Inside the Glass Door” →

514
00:34:45,784 --> 00:34:50,222
I wonder if he'll reach that pillar.

515
00:34:50,289 --> 00:34:53,225
(Luna) I was taken right on board.

516
00:34:53,292 --> 00:34:57,729
Fujiko-san might be laughing, but one of them was taken away.

517
00:34:57,796 --> 00:34:59,798
>> Hehe…｡

518
00:35:03,302 --> 00:35:07,306
The old man was doing something drowsy.

519
00:35:13,312 --> 00:35:16,248
When we renovated →

520
00:35:16,315 --> 00:35:19,751
I said, "Why don't you buy a new table?"

521
00:35:19,818 --> 00:35:24,323
But my mom said, ``It's fine the way it is.''

522
00:35:27,826 --> 00:35:30,262
It's nostalgic.

523
00:35:30,329 --> 00:35:35,767
When I was a kid, we had a birthday party every year.

524
00:35:35,834 --> 00:35:40,205
(Young Nanako and others) [Happy birthday, mom! ]

525
00:35:40,272 --> 00:35:43,208
[Sound of breathing] [Yes, present! ]

526
00:35:43,275 --> 00:35:46,211
[Wow~ Thank you! ]

527
00:35:46,278 --> 00:35:48,213
[I'll take it! ]

528
00:35:48,280 --> 00:35:51,216
〔a little bit! I'll have to set it apart.]

529
00:35:51,283 --> 00:35:53,218
[Oh, no! ]

530
00:35:53,285 --> 00:35:55,721
[Good morning] [Good morning]

531
00:35:55,787 --> 00:35:58,223
[Sit down and eat, bad manners]

532
00:35:58,290 --> 00:36:00,225
[Mom, I wish it was half-cooked]

533
00:36:00,292 --> 00:36:02,227
[Then make it yourself]

534
00:36:02,294 --> 00:36:04,229
[Let's go! 〕 〔Take care〕

535
00:36:04,296 --> 00:36:07,232
[Oh, I forgot my lunch box! ] [Ah, thank you]

536
00:36:07,299 --> 00:36:10,235
[Yes, mom, please eat first.]

537
00:36:10,302 --> 00:36:13,238
[Thank you.] (Nanako) [Yes]

538
00:36:13,305 --> 00:36:37,763
♪～

539
00:36:37,829 --> 00:36:41,199
(Nanako) Hey.

540
00:36:41,266 --> 00:36:45,203
Once a year is fine →

541
00:36:45,270 --> 00:36:50,776
Can the three of us meet here?

542
00:36:54,279 --> 00:36:56,281
(Mioko) Yeah...｡

543
00:36:59,284 --> 00:37:04,222
At first, I had no intention of registering the marriage.

544
00:37:04,289 --> 00:37:08,727
Just stay by her side until the end of her life →

545
00:37:08,794 --> 00:37:12,230
If you can help me, that's fine.

546
00:37:12,297 --> 00:37:17,235
But one day she said something to me.

547
00:37:17,302 --> 00:37:19,805
(Fujiko) [Keisuke]

548
00:37:23,809 --> 00:37:26,244
[Will you marry me? ]

549
00:37:26,311 --> 00:37:28,246
〔picture? ]

550
00:37:28,313 --> 00:37:32,751
[I knew it would get you into trouble, but →

551
00:37:32,818 --> 00:37:38,757
I wanted to focus on what I wanted to do now.]

552
00:37:40,259 --> 00:37:43,695
(Ryoko) What do I want to do...

553
00:37:43,762 --> 00:37:45,697
>> Yes.

554
00:37:45,764 --> 00:37:52,204
He was a wonderful person who was a waste to me.

555
00:37:52,270 --> 00:37:58,210
(Ryoko) Keisuke who made his girlfriend's wish come true is also wonderful.

556
00:37:58,276 --> 00:38:03,215
>> No, that's not the case.

557
00:38:03,281 --> 00:38:08,286
Why do you think I hid the will?

558
00:38:10,789 --> 00:38:15,227
There's another reason.

559
00:38:15,293 --> 00:38:17,729
"Kin-kun.

560
00:38:17,796 --> 00:38:25,237
The sight of money instantly turns any prince into a villain."

561
00:38:25,303 --> 00:38:30,242
(Luna) These are the words of the teacher who appears in ``Kokoro.''

562
00:38:30,308 --> 00:38:33,812
>> It's true that I loved Fujiko-san.

563
00:38:35,313 --> 00:38:40,686
But I'm not a saint either.

564
00:38:40,752 --> 00:38:43,188
100 million or 200 million →

565
00:38:43,255 --> 00:38:47,192
When you see the numbers that will change your life →

566
00:38:47,259 --> 00:38:54,199
You may lose your rationality and want money.

567
00:38:54,266 --> 00:38:56,702
(Luna) While I still have reason →

568
00:38:56,768 --> 00:39:00,706
Have you considered losing your inheritance status?

569
00:39:00,772 --> 00:39:05,777
>>Humans are weak.

570
00:39:07,279 --> 00:39:11,717
(Luna) Fujiko-san said this before she was alive.

571
00:39:11,783 --> 00:39:16,221
>> [I don't trust men anymore]

572
00:39:16,288 --> 00:39:18,223
[More like this→

573
00:39:18,290 --> 00:39:22,794
I'm happiest when I'm talking about things I like with my friends.

574
00:39:25,297 --> 00:39:30,736
(Luna) The ``Kokoro'' teacher couldn't trust himself or anyone else.

575
00:39:30,802 --> 00:39:36,308
But in the end, I decided to believe in the main character.

576
00:39:37,809 --> 00:39:41,179
I think Fujiko was the same way.

577
00:39:41,246 --> 00:39:43,682
I decided to remarry →

578
00:39:43,749 --> 00:39:48,687
Because I finally met someone I want to believe in.

579
00:39:48,754 --> 00:40:17,215
♪～

580
00:40:17,282 --> 00:40:22,721
(Ryoko) ⟨Keisuke-san chose Fujiko's keepsake identification book⟩

581
00:40:22,788 --> 00:40:26,224
⟨Mom is “inside the glass door”⟩

582
00:40:26,291 --> 00:40:29,795
⟨I am a cat⟩

583
00:40:34,800 --> 00:40:38,737
(Ryoko) Did you come up with a password?

584
00:40:38,804 --> 00:40:41,740
(Luna) Maybe it's because I went to visit Fujiko-san.

585
00:40:41,807 --> 00:40:45,243
The cat that became the model for “I am a cat” →

586
00:40:45,310 --> 00:40:47,746
Maybe it was the day he died.

587
00:40:47,813 --> 00:40:49,748
(Ryoko) Death anniversary?

588
00:40:49,815 --> 00:40:56,254
(Luna) The cat passed away on September 13, 1909.

589
00:40:56,321 --> 00:41:02,761
１ ９ ０ ８→

590
00:41:02,828 --> 00:41:10,335
０ ９ １ ３｡

591
00:41:13,839 --> 00:41:15,273
(Monitor) (Error sound)

592
00:41:15,340 --> 00:41:18,276
(Luna) Is that wrong? (Ryoko) Huh...｡

593
00:41:18,343 --> 00:41:22,848
You have two more chances. (Luna) That's right.

594
00:41:24,850 --> 00:41:27,285
(Ryoko) Hey, Mom.

595
00:41:27,352 --> 00:41:32,791
What are you going to do if you can't open this computer?

596
00:41:32,858 --> 00:41:35,794
(Luna) What should I do...?

597
00:41:35,861 --> 00:41:41,800
📱(vibration sound)

598
00:41:43,301 --> 00:41:46,238
(Luna) Yes, Ma-kun?

599
00:41:46,304 --> 00:41:49,241
(Masayoshi) My uncle's condition suddenly changed!

600
00:41:49,307 --> 00:41:50,742
(Luna) Huh?

601
00:41:50,809 --> 00:41:52,310
>> \I'll take it down/

602
00:41:53,812 --> 00:41:58,250
Dad, stay strong! >> Eisuke Nomiya 67 years old...

603
00:41:58,316 --> 00:42:01,753
He has now been rushed to Nonomiya Hospital.

604
00:42:01,820 --> 00:42:05,323
(Luna) Thank you for contacting me. That's it.

605
00:42:06,825 --> 00:42:09,828
(Ryoko) It's tough! Emergency transportation...

606
00:42:13,832 --> 00:42:16,768
(Ryoko) Mom? Are you not going?

607
00:42:16,835 --> 00:42:18,770
(Luna) There's no way you can go.

608
00:42:18,837 --> 00:42:20,839
(Ryoko) Why?

609
00:42:24,342 --> 00:42:29,781
(Ryoko) Don't worry about it anymore!

610
00:42:29,848 --> 00:42:33,785
Mom, you can't run away!

611
00:42:33,852 --> 00:42:35,787
From my father's true intentions →

612
00:42:35,854 --> 00:42:40,292
Isn't it up to Mom what she wants now?

613
00:42:42,794 --> 00:42:45,230
That day→

614
00:42:45,297 --> 00:42:48,733
Thanks to my mom for taking me out to Osaka →

615
00:42:48,800 --> 00:42:52,804
I was able to move forward.

616
00:42:54,806 --> 00:42:57,242
Until I went on that journey →

617
00:42:57,309 --> 00:43:01,246
It's like my clock has stopped forever

618
00:43:01,313 --> 00:43:06,318
Mom's time also seems to have stopped.

619
00:43:08,820 --> 00:43:12,757
Hey...→

620
00:43:12,824 --> 00:43:15,260
What does mom want to do?

621
00:43:15,327 --> 00:43:32,277
♪～

622
00:43:32,344 --> 00:43:35,280
>> Please wait here.

623
00:43:35,347 --> 00:43:36,848
father!

624
00:43:39,284 --> 00:43:41,219
(Ryoko) Mama.

625
00:43:41,286 --> 00:43:50,729
♪～

626
00:43:50,795 --> 00:43:53,732
(Luna) Bubbly-chan shop please.

627
00:43:53,798 --> 00:43:59,237
(Ryoko) ⟨What lies ahead is hope or despair→

628
00:43:59,304 --> 00:44:02,807
I'm on mom's side⟩

629
00:44:04,809 --> 00:44:08,813
⟨I'll be by your side no matter what⟩

630
00:44:10,315 --> 00:44:12,250
(Luna) Thank you.

631
00:44:12,317 --> 00:44:22,827
♪～
